so highlight the many common traits of all three groups. This comparative look at vaqueros, cowboys, and buckaroos brings the mythical image of the American cowboy into focus and detail and honors the regional and national variations. It will be an essential resource for anyone who would know or portray the cowboy—readers, writers, songwriters, and actors among them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aCowboys -- West (U.S.) -- History. 0aCowboys -- West (U.S.) -- Pictorial works. 0aCowboys -- West (U.S.) -- Social life and customs. 0aCowboyszWest (U.S.)vPictorial works. 0aCowboyszWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aCowboyszWest (U.S.)xSocial life and customs. 0aRanch life -- Mexico. 0aRanch life -- Southwest, New. 0aRanch life -- West (U.S.). 0aRanch lifezMexico. 0aRanch lifezSouthwest, New. 0aRanch lifezWest (U.S.). 0aWest (U.S.) -- Social life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aClayton, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoy, Jim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHoy, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUnderwood, Jerald, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aUnderwood, Jerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292757981423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292757981/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK